@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Calculator {
  + add(a: numeric, b: numeric): numeric
  + subtract(a: numeric, b: numeric): numeric
  + multiply(a: numeric, b: numeric): numeric
  + divide(a: numeric, b: numeric): numeric
}

note right of Calculator::divide
  Raises ZeroDivisionError when b == 0.
  Behavior is provided natively by
  Python's / operator — no explicit
  guard is required in the implementation.
end note

@enduml
